First Read: 14-Jan-26
HB208 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2 To propose an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
3 of 2022, relating to Walker County, to authorize a person to
4 be elected or appointed as judge of probate of the county who
5 is not over 75 years of age at the time of qualifying for
6 election or appointment.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
8 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
9 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
10 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
11 Notwithstanding the provision of Section 155 of the
12 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, a person who is not over 75
13 years of age at the beginning time of qualifying for election,
14 or at the time of his or her appointment, may be elected or
15 appointed to the Office of Judge of Probate of Walker County.
16 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
17 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
18 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
19 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
20 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
21 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
22 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
23 internal or external citations and cross-references; and
24 translate effective dates.
25 END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
26 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
27 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284, 284.01, and 285
28 of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
Page 1

of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
HB208 Enrolled
29 of this state. The appropriate election official shall assign
30 a ballot number for the proposed constitutional amendment on
31 the election ballot and shall set forth the following
32 description of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
33 constitutional amendment:
34 "Relating to Walker County, proposing an amendment to
35 the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to set the maximum age at
36 which a person may qualify as judge of probate of the county
37 to the age of 75 years at the time of qualifying for election
38 or appointment.
39 Proposed by Act ____."
40 This description shall be followed by the following
41 language:
42 "Yes( ) No( )."
43 Section 3. The proposed amendment shall become valid as
44 part of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, when approved by
45 a majority of the qualified electors voting thereon.
